ingredientsDesc:
A. Estradiol Standards:
One vial, 2.0 mL, labeled A, containing 0 pg/mL estradiol and six vials, 1 mL each, labeled B-G, containing concentrations of approximately 5, 10, 20, 50, 250 and 750 pg/mL (0.018-2.78 nmol/L) estradiol in serum. 
B. Estradiol [I-125] Reagent: (YELLOW)
One vial, 11 mL, containing < 5 μCi(185 kBq) of [I-125]-labeled estradiol in a protein-based (BSA) buffer. 
C. Estradiol Antiserum: (BLUE)
One vial, 11 mL, containing rabbit anti-estradiol (polyclonal) serum in a protein-based (BSA) buffer. 
D. Precipitating Reagent:
One bottle, 100 mL, containing goat anti-rabbit gamma globulin serum in a buffer with polyethylene glycol as a precipitating aid. 
E. Estradiol Controls:
Two vials, levels I and II, containing low and high concentrations of estradiol in serum.
